The paper deals with camera pose estimation from a single image and a 3D model, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of mixture models and robust objective functions suggests a focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically found in the cs.CV and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of branch-and-bound and novel bounds suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms, which are typically found in the cs.RO and cs.GR sub-categories. Finally, the incorporation of side information such as semantic labels suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which is typically found in the cs.AI sub-category.
